##Everyone who has left this winter has lived in the heat of the moment

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

The following article was written by the author, Mirror Image Studio

The author platform of thepaper.cn | a wider world and a more fruitful life

HTTP: www.thepaper.cn

Today, a month has passed since the city of Wuhan was closed. On January 23rd the dockside city of 10m people plunged into a whirlpool, from the Battle of Gaixia to the Far East, and countless people joined forces to turn the tide.

Within a short period of time, the epidemic spread from Wuhan to the whole country. As of 2400 hours on 22 February, 2,442 confirmed cases of NCP had died. In addition, there are many people who have left because of the epidemic. Here, we try to document the lives that were stopped by the epidemic. Some of them are ordinary people, some died in the fight against the epidemic, is a doctor, volunteers, but also a pity educators... through these life, is a very important life.

Benevolence

In the whirlpool, they are drops of water against the current.

After the closure of the city, the public transport system in Wuhan was almost disrupted, and the commuting of medical staff became a problem. He Hui joined the team of volunteers and volunteered to transport medical staff to and from work. He explained to his family that it was important. It was in keeping with his usual warm and kind nature, and he was the man of the House. The last time the family saw him was on February 2, at the Tongji Hospital Clinic. He Hui, who had been infected, got into an ambulance to be transferred to the hospital. He waved to his family, showing calm and strength. The funeral home received the body of He Hui, a 1965-year-old ferry man, from Tongji Hospital's sino-french new town compound on the night of March 3. The death certificate read "Respiratory System Exhaustion" .

Before Xu Peng went out, he said to his son, "daddy went to fight the monster. ". With his handsome back hair and short beard, he is a heroic father and the captain of the Jiangsu Blue Sky rescue team. He has carried out rescue missions for the cyclone in Funing, the shipwreck in Guangyuan, the snowstorm in Yushu and even in Burma, Laos and Hoh Xil. From February 7, he is in charge of the Tianhe Airport Emergency Warehouse to major hospitals from the global distribution of anti-epidemic donations. On February 10th, while carrying supplies, he did not escape an accidental car accident. The ROC flies high, the soul returns to the blue sky.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xu Peng (Source: Suzhou Evening News)

In 2005, Yu Guanrong, a Wuhan native, lost his son in an accident, which was the reason he decided to become a rescuer. He is a keen winter swimmer and in 2010 launched the Yangtze Rescue Team. He has rescued at least a dozen people from the Yangtze, Han River and East L. in the past decade. He is a life-fearing person, does not smoke does not drink, the friend circle signature says "health first" , usually can hold in the water 3 minutes 20 seconds, the vital capacity is astonishing. His micro blog is called "big something" , which means a stone post at the bottom of a pillar, meaning firm and stable. He died on February 6 because of new coronary pneumonia.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yu Guanrong

Ordinary people

More Wuhan people, they live the most common livelihood, daily by trivial occupied energy. Hot or cold, just be alive. Every year is like this, and this New Year should be like this.

January 28 is the 70th birthday of Wuhan Resident Jiang Shouchang. It was five days after Wuhan closed down, but Jiang Xiaohui managed to order a cake. Her birthday was only three days away from her father's, and they celebrated together. He worked as a technician, then developed throat cancer, survived, and switched to logistics. The days are over. Since his stroke, he has stayed home, watching cop shows and war movies, and maintaining a quiet old age. But a birthday is, after all, a day of rejoicing. Jiang Xiaohui is confident that his father will survive his 69th birthday and his 70th, and there will be plenty of time. Three days later, however, he developed a high fever and was later diagnosed with new crown pneumonia. On February 10th, his heart stopped.

Once upon a time, Lin once ran a wax-up shop on the Poyang Street. Most of the staff at Wuhan Central Hospital are his regular customers. They used to go to his shop on credit and buy a late supper on the night shift. The black-faced boss, with a smiling face, readily to help deliver goods to the door, send and receive express delivery. The concession stand is his business and his residence. He's guarding the hospital. No one knows when he was infected. Since January 31, he has been confined to a makeshift hospital bed, barely surviving without effective medical care. It was not until February 9 that he was able to find a bed, and that evening his condition deteriorated beyond the call of duty. "We are all little people, " Cai Yi, director of the Pain Department at Wuhan Central Hospital, wrote to the old friend, who did not have time to get to know him well. "We are all little people. Under the baptism of this epidemic, we are silently giving and silently enduring life and death. "

Qiu Jun's death is even more difficult for relatives and friends to accept. Although over 70 years old, but has been a fitness master, but also won the honor of fitness champion. More than a decade ago, his wife died, because of the hobby of fitness, old age is not lonely. His routine of going to parks and gyms is a testament to his unstinting display of brawn and brawn. Even on January 23rd, when the city was shut down, he went to the park to exercise, as he always did. On January 24th he began to feel unusually ill, and was admitted 11 days later with a new case of pneumonia. He was hospitalized for three days before he died. Family knows, after all, 72 years old, no matter how strong muscles, also can not bear the age in here.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Qiu Jun (source: ifeng.com)

Qu Qiaoming left on February 6th, his consciousness was already unclear before he died, and he didn't know what happened outside. His family remembers him as a man in high spirits. As a young man, he worked as a laborer at Wuqiao Heavy Industry. He's a tough guy. He drinks and he's a jerk. Old Wife Yang Laiyun often sighs softly to say the fate is bitter, how to marry such a person. Old Temper seems to be better, learn to do northern food, in their own roof to serve flowers, a dog. Later, after a stroke, hearing and kidney problems, and gradually unable to move. For six years, I've been lying in bed, turning over every day by my children, doing this and that. Children are bound to have resentment and quarrel with the old man. But the obligation to do, the suffering, is always recognized. Originally, he was suffering from common pneumonia, January 16 by the family rushed to the Emergency Room in concord, they do not have the knowledge to prevent cross-infection. In hindsight, this may have been where the new coronavirus infiltrated the old man's fragile body.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the Spring Festival of 2010, Qu Qiaoming, Yang Laiyun and their daughter made dumplings together

Yu Ming also worked as a factory worker all his life and retired in 2000. Every once in a while, someone asks him for a job, and he takes it. He is honest, few words, and his wife are simple people, retired to go out early to buy food. They are the most typical ordinary people, no special interests, most of the time just sitting at home watching television, in the community, Hoida, chat. On the third day of the Lunar New Year, he did not feel strange, but the son to be on the safe side, to his father took the temperature, really hit. The family took him to a community hospital, where they took a scan, found a double lung infection, and diagnosed him with viral pneumonia. On February 10, he was on his way to Vulcan Mountain Hospital, and he took his last breath.

Liu Zhiying was one of the first group of hydropower engineers after the founding of the People's Republic of China. His wife, Hu Mei, followed him into Tibet, where she worked as a Barefoot doctor in Lhasa and as a financial accountant. His son, Liu Gang, was born in Lhasa in 1970. The family returned to Wuhan in 1979. Liu Zhangying is the backbone of the family, is a transparent people, leading the small family prospering. Over the years, the couple have been very close. Hu Chengmei is also a strong woman, easily unwilling to show weakness in front of family members. The last time I left, it was quiet. There was no noise in the bedroom. The grief of Liu Zhiying prophesies to the son, the wife leaves, own spirit also collapsed. He died three days later.

Healers

When the whistle sounded in the night sky, Li Wenliang had left. He was a man of great honesty when he gave warning of the outbreak. When you're infected, you're thinking about getting back on the line. After he left, people scoured his twitter feed, piecing together a picture of the doctor, who likes good food and is digitally controlled, and lit tiny candles at the bottom of each post in memory of an ophthalmologist who doesn't pretend to be brave.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In memory of Li Wenliang

After Li, another front-runner was Liu Zhiming, director of Wuchang Hospital in Wuhan. Li Wenliang may be able to call him a "senior" , the two students together at Wu University. Wuchang Hospital was one of the first designated hospitals in Wuhan to receive patients with fever. Liu Zhiming had entered the ICU wearing a class I protective device. There were many suspected cases of new pneumonia in the ICU. His colleagues later analyzed that the infection might have originated at that time. His wife, Cai Liping, was also a head nurse. She treated patients day and night, and when her husband collapsed, she had to rely on Wechat to ask herself: Can I go with you? I'm GonNa stay with you, okay? You want me to take care of you? No, he said yes. He lay in the ICU, in the white ward, fidgeting, Hypoxia, sweating profusely, breathing heavily and recovering for a time, thinking that he should not die. Just a few days ago, he was a member of the front line, the dean of Medicine, on call, 24 hours a day, still not enough time. Eventually, things didn't go as planned, and the doctors couldn't help themselves. On February 18, Liu Zhiming left.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Liu Zhiming

A wedding that never came was called off by the outbreak. Peng Yinhua, a doctor at the First People's Hospital in Jiangxia District, Wuhan, and his wife had planned to marry on the eighth day of the first lunar month. The situation changed, and they agreed that the epidemic would not go away and that the wedding date would be delayed. After that, he volunteered to fight the plague. He's a smoking internist. He has to deal with first-line patients. At one point, he lasted two days and two nights in a row, during which he admitted more than 40 patients. In high-intensity conditions, resistance drops without warning. On January 25, the first day of the New Year, Peng Yinhua was admitted to hospital, on February 2, he also played in the ward optimistic v-shaped gesture, let his blood plasma transfusion nurses take photos. He's ready for a victory. On February 20, Peng Yinhua left the world with unfinished wishes. In his drawer were wedding invitations that he had not had time to hand out.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Colleagues Commemorate Peng Yinhua (Source: Xinhua News Agency)

In Ezhou, Xu defu is a well-known old Chinese medicine doctor who specializes in treating liver, gall bladder, spleen and stomach diseases. He uses the medicine to be simple and inexpensive to test, the medicine gets rid of the disease, on the net even is circulating his prescription. Though retired, he was hired back as an expert by the Ezhou Hospital of Traditional Chinese Medicine, where he made weekly visits, sometimes for free. Years ago, the number of patients increased, people always say that his number is hard to get. It's also a physical and mental challenge for the 63-year-old. Hsu's route of infection remains unknown and he died on February 13. A citizen named Xia Jingming sent his poem to Florida, "the plague is blind, the good man can not live forever" .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Hui tak-fu

Duty

Mao's fall was an accident. He is the deputy director of the Central Health Center in Xianyang town, Pucheng County, Fujian, Fujian Province. He is the only deputy director of the Health Center and a general practitioner. Pucheng County, Fujian is known as the "North Gate" of Fujian Province, the province's epidemic prevention, is bound to guard the geographical location. On the first day of the Lunar New Year, it was his turn to stand guard at the monitoring point of the high-speed checkpoint. From 1600 to 2400 hours, he registered the vehicle information and checked the body temperature of the passengers. He only ate a bowl of instant noodles that night. His son was waiting for him at home. His wife was away at work and was on her way home. Afternoon before going out, he put on a new clothes, asked his son handsome, 21 pm, a car out of control hit him.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Mao's last meal was a box of instant noodles

For the past two weeks, at 5 a.m. , Jiang has been wearing a red uniform, a light blue surgical mask and carrying a box of protective equipment containing protective clothing, isolation clothing, face bottles, masks, masks, shoe covers and gloves. This is what he was wearing before he left the house. He was a physician at the Dayu County Center for Disease Control and Prevention in Ganzhou, Jiangxi Province, who was responsible for conducting epidemiological investigations in isolation wards during the outbreak. Arriving at the clean-up area of the hospital, he opened the equipment box, changed into it, and walked into the isolation room filled with the new coronavirus. In the more than 20 days since the outbreak, his main work has been to interview the patients here, to verify the basic situation of the investigation case, the course of the outbreak, the history of exposure, to identify close contacts and suspected exposed persons. The pace continued for 15 days. I don't know how much longer he would have been out of action had it not been for a heart attack from overwork on January 28.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Jiang Jinbo (first from left, Source: Economic Daily)

Acute myocardial infarction also took away the village doctor Wang Tu-cheng. He is the village doctor of Xinwangzhuang village in Changge, Henan Province. Henan's hard nuclear epidemic prevention, disassembled, is the collection of millions of water droplets. One of the rural epidemic prevention, is an important link. There's so much to be done. One by one to investigate the health of the villagers, take body temperature, guide disinfection, in the group transfer anti-epidemic knowledge, repeated report. He was scrolling down the screen, so you could hear him screaming at the other end. He has been working in the village clinic since 2005, when he was granted a village doctor's license, relieving the ailments of more than 2,000 villagers. When he was found, he was lying quietly in the rest room of this shabby room.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xinwangzhuang Village Clinic (Picture Source: People's Net)

On the first day of the first lunar month, Song Yingjie and his parents left a group photo at home. He was dressed in a pressed black windbreaker. His parents were dressed in red and jubilant clothes. This is how they should dress on the first day of the New Year. It was a poor family that grew lemon trees for a living. Song Yingjie is "90" , home children, thick eyebrows thin eyes, lean and compact, after graduating from the University of Hengshan County in Hunan Province under the town of Maji health care. It was his first day on the team fighting new crown pneumonia, and he was responsible for taking body temperature readings of people in traffic at highway tollgates. The local lack of manpower, but also take care of the distribution of materials, back and forth are so trivial and wear physical work. Eleven days later, in the early hours of the morning, he returned to the dormitory after his shift. Sudden Cardiac death quietly took the young man away.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Song Yingjie and his parents (Source: Hengyang Evening News)

Colleagues still remember the soft closing sound of Xu Hui's door when he entered the office, and the Deep Voice of Xu Hui. She is the deputy director of the Nanjing Hospital of Traditional Chinese medicine, the new champion pneumonia prevention team leader, all kinds of decisions rely on her decision-making. These days, even when she gets home, the phone keeps ringing off the hook, and the husband can only remember her worried tone, and can roughly imagine the daily grind she faces. On the morning of February 6, my colleague Tang Mubai heard Xu Hui mention that his feet were swollen. He persuaded her to have an ultrasound, but she didn't go. In the evening, in excruciating pain, she finally decided to make a fake phone call. It was the last day of her life.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Tsui Fai

Nurturer

In 1953, at the age of 19, Duan Zhengcheng became the first college student to enroll in the Huazhong University of Science and Technology. After graduating in 1957, he stayed on to teach. And he said, I have planted a tree in the garden of Yu. True to his word, when he entered the school, a group of young students were involved in infrastructure work, often planting trees in the morning and working as laborers on the construction site in the afternoon. In 1996, Duan Zhengcheng led the team to develop the world's first whole body gamma knife, greatly improving the accuracy of killing tumor cells, reducing damage to normal organs. The invention has been popularized in hundreds of hospitals all over the country. On February 15, Duan Zhengcheng died of new pneumonia. On the same day, the Huazhong University of Science and Technology announced that Mr. Duan Zhengcheng of the "Journey Grant" Department of the university had made an anonymous donation with his million-yuan prize money. What he did in life, he did on his own, Fauser.

Also leaving the Division of Wuhan Tongji Hospital Professor Lin Zhengbin. He's a low-profile transplant specialist. He graduated from Tongji Medical College in 1983 and studied at Kanazawa Medical University in Japan. He kept a low profile, was modest and soft-spoken. He has been engaged in organ transplantation for more than 30 years and is a national treasure expert. This year he is 62 years old, retired, this is the age of rest. Colleagues speculate that the professor may have been carried away by a storm of "inflammatory factors" triggered by his body. On weekdays, he is in good health, there is no basic disease, there should be a long time to enjoy a quiet old age.

In the dark background, patchwork neatly placed bright and colorful fruit. Everyday objects, through the artist's brushwork, show a solemn and peaceful sense of life. This is Liu Shouxiang's representative work "fresh fruit" . He is one of the most influential painters in Chinese contemporary watercolor painting. In 1981, he graduated from Hubei University of Fine Arts and stayed on as a teacher. He retired in 2018 and trained a large number of fine arts talents. On February 13th, he was taken from life by new crown pneumonia, and his work and artistic spirit will live on forever.

Liu Shouxiang

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Conclusion

Also killed by the new crown pneumonia and the fight against the epidemic were doctor Xiao Jun of the Wuhan Red Cross Hospital, Doctor Xia Si of the Wuhan Xiehe Jiangbei District Hospital, Doctor Jiang Jijun of the Taizhou People's Hospital, nurse Liu Fan of the Wuhan Wuchang Hospital, Director Chang Kai of the Hubei Film Studio, Professor Hong Ling of the Huake University, frontline police officers Wang Chuntian, Pan Jiming and he Jianhua, traffic Police Zheng Yong, auxiliary police Wang Ailan, grass-roots Cadres Jiang Na, Huang Heyan, government employees Li Guangjian, community doctor Song Yunhua... We can not do together all the names of those who left.

We're having a long winter. What is ahead, must be brave to go over, personally verify. No hesitation, no loss of will. There is pain and there is victory.

Only by winning the battle can we comfort everyone who has left in the winter, who has lived in the heat.
